  "prompt": "What is your review of 8 Women (2002 movie)?",
  "response": "\"8 Women\" (8 Femmes) is a French musical comedy-mystery film directed by Fran\u00e7ois Ozon, featuring an all-star cast of French actresses including Catherine Deneuve, Isabelle Huppert, Emmanuelle B\u00e9art, and others. The film is a stylish and campy homage to 1950s Hollywood melodramas and murder mysteries.\n\nThe story takes place in a snowy mansion where a wealthy man is found murdered, and eight women who are connected to him are potential suspects. Each woman gets a musical number that reveals aspects of her character and potential motives.\n\nThe film is known for its:\n- Colorful, stylized production design\n- Playful and satirical approach to the murder mystery genre\n- Excellent ensemble cast\n- Witty musical numbers\n- Tongue-in-cheek humor and camp aesthetic\n- Exploration of female relationships and secrets\n\nCritics generally praised the film for its entertainment value, performances, and unique style. It won several French film awards and was appreciated for its innovative blend of genres.\n\nWhile I can provide this overview, I want to be clear that this is a summary based on available information, not a personal review, as I don't have subjective experiences of watching movies.",
